> These power bowls are brimming with a bevy of veggies in various forms. For the base, jasmine rice is simmered with vegetable broth until tender, then mixed with ribbons of lacinato kale. On top sit sweet maple-roasted Brussels sprouts and blackened Cajun-spiced chickpeas. Everything is finished with a drizzle of Creole Dijonnaise for creamy richness and a sprinkle of toasted pecans for a buttery crunch.

Please refer to the recipe card for Step 1.

== Rice and Kale ==

In a #pot{}, simmer @jasmine rice{1/2%cup} with @veggie stock concentrate{1} and @water{2%cups} until tender.

Add @lacinato kale{2.75%oz}(chopped into ribbons) to the rice and stir to combine.

== Maple Brussels Sprouts ==

Toss @Brussels sprouts{8%oz} with @maple syrup{1%oz} and a drizzle of @cooking oil{}.

Spread the Brussels sprouts on a #baking sheet{} and roast at ~{25%minutes} until tender and caramelized.

== Cajun-Spiced Chickpeas ==

Drain and rinse @garbanzo beans{13.25%oz}.

In a #9.5-10-inch stainless steel pan{}, heat @cooking oil{} and cook the chickpeas with @blackening spices{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{} to taste.

== Assembly ==

Divide the rice and kale between #plates{}.

Top with maple Brussels sprouts and Cajun-spiced chickpeas.

Drizzle with @Creole Dijonnaise{2%oz}.

Sprinkle with @pecans{1/2%oz}(toasted).

Add a pat of @butter{1%tbsp} for extra richness if desired.